body:
In the module below, iverilog version "12.0 (devel)" on Windows run with -Wall reports warning "implicit definition of wire 'IDLE'." for the second to last line of the module below.
```
module bug(input logic clk, input logic rst);
    enum logic[0:0] {
        IDLE,
        ACTIVE
    } state;
    always @(posedge clk, negedge rst) begin
        if (rst) state <= IDLE;
        else case (state)
            IDLE: state <= ACTIVE;
            ACTIVE: state <= IDLE;
        endcase
    end
    other other(state == IDLE);  // <-- TREATS IDLE AS IMPLICIT WIRE
endmodule
```
Running the above in a test bench for a few cycles shows that iverilog includes a signal named IDLE (fixed at 1'bz) in module bug, and the input to module other is always undefined.  

Inserting line `wire is_idle = state == IDLE` and replacing `state == IDLE` in the port binding with `is_idle` eliminates the warning, the spurious IDLE signal, and undefined input to other.

